            <title>[KAFKA-17415] Avoid overflow of expiried timestamp</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/KAFKA-17415</link>
                <project id="12311720" key="KAFKA">Kafka</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Currently `DelegationTokenControlManager` does not handle the overflow, and hence setting a large max life time will cause a negative expired timestamp and negative max timestamp. That is unexpected behavior.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;0&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/kafka/blob/4e846038a6313e28d3b3ee3d3c3163d1f26356bf/metadata/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/controller/DelegationTokenControlManager.java#L188&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/kafka/blob/0123bdcf06d2554ea62ba3a75af7c4b17eb4d23a/metadata/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/controller/DelegationTokenControlManager.java#L191&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;1&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/kafka/blob/0123bdcf06d2554ea62ba3a75af7c4b17eb4d23a/core/src/main/scala/kafka/server/DelegationTokenManagerZk.scala#L297&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/kafka/blob/0123bdcf06d2554ea62ba3a75af7c4b17eb4d23a/core/src/main/scala/kafka/server/DelegationTokenManagerZk.scala#L182&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
